tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Lipid profile is within or near target ranges, with LDL at the upper limit of normal. Mild normocytic anemia is present (low erythrocytes and hematocrit, normal MCV/MCH), which may warrant further evaluation. Platelet count is normal, but platelet distribution width is elevated, possibly indicating increased platelet size variability. No acute abnormalities detected; recommend clinical correlation and follow-up for anemia.
